{"comments":"Target Resolution for Product Tours\n\nThis module provides target resolution — finding and tracking the DOM elements\nthat tour steps highlight. Targets can be:\n- CSS selectors\n- Test IDs (data-testid)\n- ARIA roles\n- Element references\n- Viewport (no element)\n- Multiple elements\n\n## Design Philosophy\n\nTarget resolution is inherently effectful (DOM access), but we describe\ntargets as pure data. The runtime performs actual resolution.\n\nMulti-element targeting supports tours that highlight groups of related\nelements (e.g., \"These are all your notification settings\").\n\n## Usage\n\n```purescript\nimport Hydrogen.Tour.Target as Target\n\n-- Single element by selector\ntarget1 = Target.bySelector \".my-button\"\n\n-- By test ID (preferred for stability)\ntarget2 = Target.byTestId \"submit-btn\"\n\n-- Multiple elements\ntarget3 = Target.multiSelector \".sidebar-item\"\n\n-- Viewport-centered modal\ntarget4 = Target.viewport\n```\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Tour","Types"],"Selector"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[122,19],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Tour/Target.purs","start":[122,3]},"title":"SingleSelector"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Tour","Types"],"TestId"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[124,17],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Tour/Target.purs","start":[124,3]},"title":"SingleTestId"},{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Tour","Types"],"AriaRole"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Maybe"],"Maybe"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},"tag":"ParensInType"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{